name: Engineering Document Register with Help Panel

textBoxes.content: This chart displays current documents (excluding supplier data) with attached transmittals to the client and Status contains "Issued" labeled as issued, while those that are still in a Reserved State, Commented Internally, or Issued for Internal Review are categorized as "In progress". Documents that are neither issued nor reserved fall under a separate category called others.
This Donut chart shows the current Issued document statuses with attached transmittals (excluding supplier data) to the client by the distinct count of document numbers.
This Donut chart shows the current IFR document status with attached transmittals (excluding supplier data) to the client by the distinct count of document numbers.

This Donut chart displays the status of current IFC documents with attached transmittals (excluding supplier data) to the client based on the distinct count of revisions and the distinct count of document numbers. If the revision count is 1, it is labeled as IFC. If the revision count is 2, it is labeled as IFC (revised 1). If the revision count is 3, it is labeled as IFC (revised 2). If the revision count is greater than 3, it is labeled as IFC (revised > 2).
This table is showing Deliverable Details.
The filters will interact will all the cards and graphical representations on the report page.
